cdx6500PPCTXDLCPortTable.name: cdx6500PPCTXDLCPortTable
cdx6500PPCTXDLCPortTable.description: All of the configuration parameters relevant to the XDLC port table.

cdx6500PPCTXDLCPortEntry.name: cdx6500PPCTXDLCPortEntry
cdx6500PPCTXDLCPortEntry.description: A row of XDLC Port configuration parameters.

cdx6500xdlcpPortControl.name: cdx6500xdlcpPortControl
cdx6500xdlcpPortControl.description: Specify any of the following port control options: NONE - no option specified. MB - raise Pin 22 when the port becomes disabled.

cdx6500xdlcpTxCoding.name: cdx6500xdlcpTxCoding
cdx6500xdlcpTxCoding.description: This is the data encoding used on the XDLC link. nrz - Non Return to Zero. nrzi - Non Return to Zero Inverted. newvalNrz - same functionality as 'nrz', new enumeration added for RFC1155 compatibility.

cdx6500xdlcpLineType.name: cdx6500xdlcpLineType
cdx6500xdlcpLineType.description: Type of line, indicates whether half duplex or full duplex signals are being generated. fdx - communications occuring in both directions simultaneously between devices. Only Full Duplex operation is currently supported.

cdx6500xdlcpTxType.name: cdx6500xdlcpTxType
cdx6500xdlcpTxType.description: This is the transmission mode used on the line. twa - Two Way Alternate used by most controllers. tws - Two Way Simultaneous. newvalTws - same functionality as 'tws', new enumeration added for RFC1155 compatibility.

cdx6500xdlcpClockSource.name: cdx6500xdlcpClockSource
cdx6500xdlcpClockSource.description: int - Internal clock source. ext - External clock source. newvalInt - same functionality as 'int', new enumeration added for RFC1155 compatibility.

cdx6500xdlcpClockSpeed.name: cdx6500xdlcpClockSpeed
cdx6500xdlcpClockSpeed.description: This is the speed of the port in bits per second, when using internal clocking.

cdx6500xdlcpStationCnt.name: cdx6500xdlcpStationCnt
cdx6500xdlcpStationCnt.description: This is the number of stations on the XDLC line.

cdx6500xdlcpPollTimer.name: cdx6500xdlcpPollTimer
cdx6500xdlcpPollTimer.description: Worst case delay for a slave to respond to a poll frame sent by the master, including modem turn around time, etc. Value in 10ths of second ( 30 = 3.0 seconds ).

cdx6500xdlcpPollPeriod.name: cdx6500xdlcpPollPeriod
cdx6500xdlcpPollPeriod.description: Time in milliseconds between polls when no data is exchanged.

cdx6500xdlcpTries.name: cdx6500xdlcpTries
cdx6500xdlcpTries.description: Maximum number of attempts to complete a transmission.

cdx6500xdlcpPortOptions.name: cdx6500xdlcpPortOptions
cdx6500xdlcpPortOptions.description: Select options on this XDLC port as follows: NONE - no option specified.

cdx6500xdlcpPortAddress.name: cdx6500xdlcpPortAddress
cdx6500xdlcpPortAddress.description: When an XDLC port makes a call, this address is inserted into the calling address field.

cdx6500xdlcpRestartTimer.name: cdx6500xdlcpRestartTimer
cdx6500xdlcpRestartTimer.description: Restart-Request timeout timer in seconds. If timer expires, request is sent again.

cdx6500xdlcpResetTimer.name: cdx6500xdlcpResetTimer
cdx6500xdlcpResetTimer.description: Reset-Request timeout timer in seconds. If timer expires, request is sent again.

cdx6500xdlcpCallTimer.name: cdx6500xdlcpCallTimer
cdx6500xdlcpCallTimer.description: Call-Request timeout timer in seconds. If timer expires, call is cleared.

cdx6500xdlcpClearTimer.name: cdx6500xdlcpClearTimer
cdx6500xdlcpClearTimer.description: Clear-Request timeout timer in seconds. If timer expires, request is sent again.

cdx6500xdlcpMaxFrameSize.name: cdx6500xdlcpMaxFrameSize
cdx6500xdlcpMaxFrameSize.description: Maximum size (in bytes) of a frame, excluding the frame header and CRC for SDLC frames. This parameter is Not effective on MX25 type stations.

cdx6500xdlcpElectricalInterfaceType.name: cdx6500xdlcpElectricalInterfaceType
cdx6500xdlcpElectricalInterfaceType.description: Specify the Electrical Interface Type: V.24 - V.24 Electrical Interface Type V.35 - V.35 Electrical Interface Type V.36 - V.36 Electrical Interface Type X.21 - X.21 Electrical Interface Type NONE - Electrically disabled

cdx6500xdlcpV24ElectricalInterfaceOption.name: cdx6500xdlcpV24ElectricalInterfaceOption
cdx6500xdlcpV24ElectricalInterfaceOption.description: Specify the Pin 22 option: RI - V.24 uses Pin 22 for Ring Indicator output signal TM - V.24 uses Pin 22 for Test Mode input signal

cdx6500xdlcpHighSpeedElectricalInterface.name: cdx6500xdlcpHighSpeedElectricalInterfaceOption
cdx6500xdlcpHighSpeedElectricalInterface.description: Specify the cable type: NONE - V.35/V.36/X.21 DCE with straight through cable XOVER - V.35/V.36/X.21 DCE with crossover adapter cable

cdx6500PPSTXDLCPortTable.name: cdx6500PPSTXDLCPortTable
cdx6500PPSTXDLCPortTable.description: All of the statistics parameters relevant to the XDLC Port table.

cdx6500PPSTXDLCPortEntry.name: cdx6500PPSTXDLCPortEntry
cdx6500PPSTXDLCPortEntry.description: A row of XDLC Port statistics parameters.

cdx6500xdlcpStatsPortNumber.name: cdx6500xdlcpStatsPortNumber
cdx6500xdlcpStatsPortNumber.description: Specifies a specific port (physical port number) in the node.

cdx6500xdlcpPortStatus.name: cdx6500xdlcpPortStatus
cdx6500xdlcpPortStatus.description: Specifies the current port status. disabled : The port is disabled by user. enabled : The port is enabled by user. busyOut : The port is busy outed by user. up : At least one station is responding to polls. down : None of the stations are responding to polls. newvalDisabled : same functionality as 'disabled', new enumeration added for RFC1155 compatibility.

cdx6500xdlcpPortSpeed.name: cdx6500xdlcpPortSpeed
cdx6500xdlcpPortSpeed.description: The measured port speed in bits per second.

cdx6500xdlcpUtilizationIn.name: cdx6500xdlcpUtilizationIn
cdx6500xdlcpUtilizationIn.description: Indicates a percentage of the port recources that are currently in use from the line to the port.

cdx6500xdlcpUtilizationOut.name: cdx6500xdlcpUtilizationOut
cdx6500xdlcpUtilizationOut.description: Indicates a percentage of the port recources that are currently in use from the port to the line.

cdx6500xdlcpCharInTotal.name: cdx6500xdlcpCharInTotal
cdx6500xdlcpCharInTotal.description: Total number of characters processed until now, not including header characters.

cdx6500xdlcpCharOutTotal.name: cdx6500xdlcpCharOutTotal
cdx6500xdlcpCharOutTotal.description: Total number of characters processed until now, not including header characters.

cdx6500xdlcpCharsInPerSec.name: cdx6500xdlcpCharsInPerSec
cdx6500xdlcpCharsInPerSec.description: The average number of characters received per second.

cdx6500xdlcpCharsOutPerSec.name: cdx6500xdlcpCharsOutPerSec
cdx6500xdlcpCharsOutPerSec.description: The average number of characters transmitted per second.

cdx6500xdlcpFrameInTotal.name: cdx6500xdlcpFrameInTotal
cdx6500xdlcpFrameInTotal.description: Total number of MX25 and SDLC frames processed until now.

cdx6500xdlcpFrameOutTotal.name: cdx6500xdlcpFrameOutTotal
cdx6500xdlcpFrameOutTotal.description: Total number of MX25 and SDLC frames processed until now.

cdx6500xdlcpFramesInPerSec.name: cdx6500xdlcpFramesInPerSec
cdx6500xdlcpFramesInPerSec.description: The average number of frames received per second.

cdx6500xdlcpFramesOutPerSec.name: cdx6500xdlcpFramesOutPerSec
cdx6500xdlcpFramesOutPerSec.description: The average number of frames transmitted per second.

cdx6500xdlcpCRCErrors.name: cdx6500xdlcpCRCErrors
cdx6500xdlcpCRCErrors.description: Total number of CRC errors counted by the I/O driver.

cdx6500xdlcpOverrunErrors.name: cdx6500xdlcpOverrunErrors
cdx6500xdlcpOverrunErrors.description: Total number of overrun errors counted by the I/O driver.

cdx6500xdlcpUnderrunErrors.name: cdx6500xdlcpUnderrunErrors
cdx6500xdlcpUnderrunErrors.description: Total number of overrun errors counted by the I/O driver.

cdx6500xdlcpRNRFramesIn.name: cdx6500xdlcpRNRFramesIn
cdx6500xdlcpRNRFramesIn.description: Indicates the total number of RNR frames received.

cdx6500xdlcpRNRFramesOut.name: cdx6500xdlcpRNRFramesOut
cdx6500xdlcpRNRFramesOut.description: Indicates the total number of RNR frames transmitted.

cdx6500xdlcpRRFramesIn.name: cdx6500xdlcpRRFramesIn
cdx6500xdlcpRRFramesIn.description: Indicates the total number of RR frames received.

cdx6500xdlcpRRFramesOut.name: cdx6500xdlcpRRFramesOut
cdx6500xdlcpRRFramesOut.description: Indicates the total number of RR frames transmitted.

cdx6500xdlcpREJFramesIn.name: cdx6500xdlcpREJFramesIn
cdx6500xdlcpREJFramesIn.description: Indicates the total number of REJ frames received.

cdx6500xdlcpREJFramesOut.name: cdx6500xdlcpREJFramesOut
cdx6500xdlcpREJFramesOut.description: Indicates the total number of REJ frames transmitted.

cdx6500xdlcpStateChange.name: cdx6500xdlcpStateChange
cdx6500xdlcpStateChange.description: The date and time when the link entered the current state.

cdx6500xdlcpLinkDowns.name: cdx6500xdlcpLinkDowns
cdx6500xdlcpLinkDowns.description: Total number of times link has made a transition from the UP state to the DOWN state.

cdx6500xdlcpPacketsQueued.name: cdx6500xdlcpPacketsQueued
cdx6500xdlcpPacketsQueued.description: Total number of packets queued at the XDLC protocol layer by the transmitter.

cdx6500xdlcpSNRMInFrames.name: cdx6500xdlcpSNRMInFrames
cdx6500xdlcpSNRMInFrames.description: Total number of SNRM frames received until the present time.

cdx6500xdlcpSNRMOutFrames.name: cdx6500xdlcpSNRMOutFrames
cdx6500xdlcpSNRMOutFrames.description: Total number of SNRM frames transmitted until the present time.

cdx6500xdlcpUAInFrames.name: cdx6500xdlcpUAInFrames
cdx6500xdlcpUAInFrames.description: Total number of UA frames received until the present time.

cdx6500xdlcpUAOutFrames.name: cdx6500xdlcpUAOutFrames
cdx6500xdlcpUAOutFrames.description: Total number of UA frames transmitted until the present time.

cdx6500xdlcpDMInFrames.name: cdx6500xdlcpDMInFrames
cdx6500xdlcpDMInFrames.description: Total number of DM frames received until the present time.

cdx6500xdlcpDMOutFrames.name: cdx6500xdlcpDMOutFrames
cdx6500xdlcpDMOutFrames.description: Total number of DM frames transmitted until the present time.

cdx6500xdlcpXIDInFrames.name: cdx6500xdlcpXIDInFrames
cdx6500xdlcpXIDInFrames.description: Total number of XID frames received until the present time.

cdx6500xdlcpXIDOutFrames.name: cdx6500xdlcpXIDOutFrames
cdx6500xdlcpXIDOutFrames.description: Total number of XID frames transmitted until the present time.

cdx6500xdlcpDISCInFrames.name: cdx6500xdlcpDISCInFrames
cdx6500xdlcpDISCInFrames.description: Total number of DISC frames received until the present time.

cdx6500xdlcpDISCOutFrames.name: cdx6500xdlcpDISCOutFrames
cdx6500xdlcpDISCOutFrames.description: Total number of DISC frames transmitted until the present time.

cdx6500xdlcpRDInFrames.name: cdx6500xdlcpRDInFrames
cdx6500xdlcpRDInFrames.description: Total number of RD frames received until the present time.

cdx6500xdlcpRDOutFrames.name: cdx6500xdlcpRDOutFrames
cdx6500xdlcpRDOutFrames.description: Total number of RD frames transmitted until the present time.

cdx6500xdlcpFRMRInFrames.name: cdx6500xdlcpFRMRInFrames
cdx6500xdlcpFRMRInFrames.description: Total number of FRMR frames received until the present time.

cdx6500xdlcpFRMROutFrames.name: cdx6500xdlcpFRMROutFrames
cdx6500xdlcpFRMROutFrames.description: Total number of FRMR frames transmitted until the present time.

cdx6500xdlcpUPInFrames.name: cdx6500xdlcpUPInFrames
cdx6500xdlcpUPInFrames.description: Total number of UP frames received until the present time.

cdx6500xdlcpUPOutFrames.name: cdx6500xdlcpUPOutFrames
cdx6500xdlcpUPOutFrames.description: Total number of UP frames transmitted until the present time.

cdx6500xdlcpTESTInFrames.name: cdx6500xdlcpTESTInFrames
cdx6500xdlcpTESTInFrames.description: Total number of TEST frames received until the present time.

cdx6500xdlcpTESTOutFrames.name: cdx6500xdlcpTESTOutFrames
cdx6500xdlcpTESTOutFrames.description: Total number of TEST frames transmitted until the present time.

cdx6500xdlcpXIDNullInFrames.name: cdx6500xdlcpXIDNullInFrames
cdx6500xdlcpXIDNullInFrames.description: Total number of XID Null frames received until the present time.

cdx6500xdlcpXIDNullOutFrames.name: cdx6500xdlcpXIDNullOutFrames

cdx6500xdlcpXID0InFrames.name: cdx6500xdlcpXID0InFrames
cdx6500xdlcpXID0InFrames.description: Total number of XID Type 0 frames received until the present time.

cdx6500xdlcpXID0OutFrames.name: cdx6500xdlcpXID0OutFrames
cdx6500xdlcpXID0OutFrames.description: Total number of XID Type 0 frames transmitted until the present time.

cdx6500xdlcpXID1InFrames.name: cdx6500xdlcpXID1InFrames
cdx6500xdlcpXID1InFrames.description: Total number of XID Type 1 frames received until the present time.

cdx6500xdlcpXID1OutFrames.name: cdx6500xdlcpXID1OutFrames
cdx6500xdlcpXID1OutFrames.description: Total number of XID Type 1 frames transmitted until the present time.

cdx6500xdlcpXID3InFrames.name: cdx6500xdlcpXID3InFrames
cdx6500xdlcpXID3InFrames.description: Total number of XID Type 3 frames received until the present time.

cdx6500xdlcpXID3OutFrames.name: cdx6500xdlcpXID3OutFrames
cdx6500xdlcpXID3OutFrames.description: Total number of XID Type 3 frames transmitted until the present time.

cdx6500SPCTXDLCStnTable.name: cdx6500SPCTXDLCStnTable
cdx6500SPCTXDLCStnTable.description: All of the configuration parameters relevant to the XDLC station table.

cdx6500SPCTXDLCStnEntry.name: cdx6500SPCTXDLCStnEntry
cdx6500SPCTXDLCStnEntry.description: A row of XDLC station configuration parameters.

cdx6500xdlcsCfgStationNumber.name: cdx6500xdlcsCfgStationNumber
cdx6500xdlcsCfgStationNumber.description: The number of the station on the multidrop line. Also used for routing purposes.

cdx6500xdlcsStationType.name: cdx6500xdlcsStationType
cdx6500xdlcsStationType.description: Enter the type of station to configure. sdlc - SDLC Station. mx25 - MX25 Station. newvalSdlc - same functionality as 'sdlc', new enumeration added for RFC1155 compatibility.

cdx6500SPCTXDLCSDLCStnTable.name: cdx6500SPCTXDLCSDLCStnTable
cdx6500SPCTXDLCSDLCStnTable.description: All of the configuration parameters relevant to the XDLC SDLC station table.

cdx6500SPCTXDLCSDLCStnEntry.name: cdx6500SPCTXDLCSDLCStnEntry
cdx6500SPCTXDLCSDLCStnEntry.description: A row of XDLC SDLC station configuration parameters.

cdx6500xdlcsdlcCfgStationNum.name: cdx6500xdlcsdlcCfgStationNum
cdx6500xdlcsdlcCfgStationNum.description: The number of the station on the multidrop line. Also used for routing purposes.

cdx6500xdlcsdlcStationAddress.name: cdx6500xdlcsdlcStationAddress
cdx6500xdlcsdlcStationAddress.description: The station address on the multidrop line.

cdx6500xdlcsdlcFrameWinSize.name: cdx6500xdlcsdlcFrameWinSize
cdx6500xdlcsdlcFrameWinSize.description: Frame level window size must be set to the same value in devices at each end of the link.

cdx6500xdlcsdlcAutocallMnem.name: cdx6500xdlcsdlcAutocallMnem
cdx6500xdlcsdlcAutocallMnem.description: This mnemonic references the remote address which will be called when polling activity is detected on the sdlc line.

cdx6500xdlcsdlcProtocolID.name: cdx6500xdlcsdlcProtocolID
cdx6500xdlcsdlcProtocolID.description: The protocol identifier is the first four bytes of the call user data. If not configured the PAD will use C3000000 as the protocol ID in the call.

cdx6500xdlcsdlcCUG.name: cdx6500xdlcsdlcCUG
cdx6500xdlcsdlcCUG.description: The station may be a member of up to 8 different Closed User Groups (CUGs). Each CUG membership must be a two digit number, separated by a comma. (e.g. 12,34,56,09,02,03). Two hyphens following each other indicate no CUG Membership. 00-99 - CUG Membership.

cdx6500xdlcsdlcOptions.name: cdx6500xdlcsdlcOptions
cdx6500xdlcsdlcOptions.description: Select options on this SDLC station as follows: NONE - no option specified CUG - check closed user group in incoming calls, and insert closed user group facility in outgoing calls. QRRs - HPAD sends QRR after QLLC link comes up XIDs - TPAD responds to QXIDs with XID configured for this station. XIDs are not sent to the Cluster Controller. XID3 - HPAD and TPAD will pass XIDs transparently, This option should not be set if XIDs option is selected. Corresponding station options must be XID3. DISCs - TPAD sends a DISC frame when station goes down. The DISC may be retransmitted up to Tries times, if the Cluster Controller does not respond, before sending a SNRM. RNRs - TPAD initially polls with RNR until a data packet or an QRR is received by the QLLC station on the TPAD side. DFC - the station will wait the amount of time specified by the call timer before placing the first call.

cdx6500xdlcsdlcXID.name: cdx6500xdlcsdlcXID
cdx6500xdlcsdlcXID.description: With this option selected, the TPAD's response to a QXID will contain the XID identification value defined in this parameter instead of from an exchange of identifications with the cluster controller. XIDs are not sent to the cluster controller.

cdx6500xdlcsdlcStnSubaddress.name: cdx6500xdlcsdlcStnSubaddress
cdx6500xdlcsdlcStnSubaddress.description: The calling subaddress is appended to the port address to create the calling address in the autocall generated.

cdx6500xdlcsdlcBillingRecords.name: cdx6500xdlcsdlcBillingRecords
cdx6500xdlcsdlcBillingRecords.description: This controls whether billing (accounting) records will be created for calls on this port. newvalOff - same functionality as 'off', new enumeration added for RFC1155 compatibility.

cdx6500xdlcsdlcProtectionLevel.name: cdx6500xdlcsdlcProtectionLevel
cdx6500xdlcsdlcProtectionLevel.description: This specifies the level of data or connection protection which will be applied to calls to or from this port. The actual level for a call will be negotiated to the lesser of this level and the level configured for the other end of the call. none - No protection. cpOnly - Connection protection only. fullDcp - Full data and connection protection. newvalNone - same functionality as 'none', new enumeration added for RFC1155 compatibility.

cdx6500xdlcsdlcReconnectTimeout.name: cdx6500xdlcsdlcReconnectTimeout
cdx6500xdlcsdlcReconnectTimeout.description: This specifies the number of seconds that DCP on the originating side will wait between reconnection attempts.

cdx6500xdlcsdlcReconnectLimit.name: cdx6500xdlcsdlcReconnectLimit
cdx6500xdlcsdlcReconnectLimit.description: This specifies the number of times that DCP on the originating side will attempt to reconnect before clearing the call. If 0 is entered, it will not attempt to reconnect.

cdx6500xdlcsdlcCallTimer.name: cdx6500xdlcsdlcCallTimer
cdx6500xdlcsdlcCallTimer.description: This specifies the time before the next call is made. If 0 is entered, the time to the next call is handled internally. The time is in seconds.

cdx6500xdlcsdlcIdleTimer.name: cdx6500xdlcsdlcIdleTimer
cdx6500xdlcsdlcIdleTimer.description: The Link Idle Timer is used by the SNA Dial on Demand feature for determining how long the station should wait for a data frame before bringing the X.25 call down. If a 0 is entered, the call will never be brought down. The time is in seconds.

cdx6500xdlcsdlcVerConnTimer.name: cdx6500xdlcsdlcVerConnTimer
cdx6500xdlcsdlcVerConnTimer.description: The Verify Connection Timer is used by the SNA Dial on Demand feature for periodically verifying that the connection to the remote station is still active, after the link has been suspended. The timer specifies how long the the station waits before verifying the connection. If a 0 is entered, the connection will never be verified. The time is in seconds.

cdx6500xdlcsdlcUnsusWaitTimer.name: cdx6500xdlcsdlcUnsusWaitTimer
cdx6500xdlcsdlcUnsusWaitTimer.description: The Unsuspend Wait Timer is used by the SNA Dial on Demand feature for determining how long the station will wait in LINK-UNSUSPENDING state after receiving a call request before bringing the station down. If a 0 is entered, the station waits in LINK-UNSUSPENDED state forever. Time is in seconds.

cdx6500SPCTXDLCMX25StnTable.name: cdx6500SPCTXDLCMX25StnTable
cdx6500SPCTXDLCMX25StnTable.description: All of the configuration parameters relevant to the XDLC MX.25 station table.

cdx6500SPCTXDLCMX25StnEntry.name: cdx6500SPCTXDLCMX25StnEntry
cdx6500SPCTXDLCMX25StnEntry.description: A row of XDLC MX.25 station configuration parameters.

cdx6500xdlcmx25CfgStationNum.name: cdx6500xdlcmx25CfgStationNum
cdx6500xdlcmx25CfgStationNum.description: The number of the station on the multidrop line. Also used for routing purposes.

cdx6500xdlcmx25StationAddress.name: cdx6500xdlcmx25StationAddress
cdx6500xdlcmx25StationAddress.description: The station address on the multidrop line.

cdx6500xdlcmx25PVCChannels.name: cdx6500xdlcmx25PVCChannels
cdx6500xdlcmx25PVCChannels.description: Number of logical channels used for Permanent Virtual Circuits. The total number of PVC and SVC channels on a link should be kept as small as possible and consistent with needs. PVC connections must be configured in the PVC Table.

cdx6500xdlcmx25StartingPVC.name: cdx6500xdlcmx25StartingPVC
cdx6500xdlcmx25StartingPVC.description: This is the starting logical channel number for the Permanent Virtual Circuits on this link. Not used if the number of PVCs = 0.

cdx6500xdlcmx25SVCChannels.name: cdx6500xdlcmx25SVCChannels
cdx6500xdlcmx25SVCChannels.description: Number of logical channels used in Switched Virtual Circuits. The total number of PVC and SVC channels on a link should be kept as small as possible and consistent with needs.

cdx6500xdlcmx25StartingSVC.name: cdx6500xdlcmx25StartingSVC
cdx6500xdlcmx25StartingSVC.description: This is the starting logical channel number for the Switched Virtual Circuits on this link. Not used if the number of SVCs = 0.

cdx6500xdlcmx25FrameWinSize.name: cdx6500xdlcmx25FrameWinSize
cdx6500xdlcmx25FrameWinSize.description: Frame level window size must be set to the same value in devices at each end of the link.

cdx6500xdlcmx25PacketWinSize.name: cdx6500xdlcmx25PacketWinSize
cdx6500xdlcmx25PacketWinSize.description: Packet level window size must be set to the same value in devices at each end of the link.

cdx6500xdlcmx25Options.name: cdx6500xdlcmx25Options
cdx6500xdlcmx25Options.description: Select options on this MX.25 port as follows: NONE - no option specified. HOLD - hold calls over link restart. CUG - check closed user group; otherwise, CUG passes transparently. INL - inter-node link. Link goes to another 6500 device. DELAY - enable delay path trace on this link. (link must be connected to Rel. 4.xx node) Any combination of the above specified by summing (e.g. HOLD+CUG+. . .).

cdx6500xdlcmx25RCDestination.name: cdx6500xdlcmx25RCDestination
cdx6500xdlcmx25RCDestination.description: All calls entering this port will be routed to the destination specified in this parameter, irrespective of route selection table entries. For example, to route calls to port 1, use P1. To route calls to port 2, station 4, use P2S4. Blank this field to disable this function.

cdx6500xdlcmx25CUG.name: cdx6500xdlcmx25CUG
cdx6500xdlcmx25CUG.description: The port may be a member of up to 8 different Closed User Groups (CUGs). Each CUG membership must be a two digit number (except --) and separated by a comma. (e.g. 12,34,56,09,02,03). -- - No CUG Membership 00-99 - CUG Membership

cdx6500xdlcmx25BillingRecords.name: cdx6500xdlcmx25BillingRecords
cdx6500xdlcmx25BillingRecords.description: This controls whether billing (accounting) records will be created for calls on this port. newvalOff - same functionality as 'off', new enumeration added for RFC1155 compatibility.

cdx6500xdlcmx25UpperQueue.name: cdx6500xdlcmx25UpperQueue
cdx6500xdlcmx25UpperQueue.description: This is the maximum number of data packets a channel on this port will queue for transmission before invoking flow control to the attached channel.

cdx6500xdlcmx25LowerQueue.name: cdx6500xdlcmx25LowerQueue
cdx6500xdlcmx25LowerQueue.description: This is the number of data packets a channel on this port will have queued for transmission when it releases flow control to the attached channel.

cdx6500SPSTXDLCSDLCStnTable.name: cdx6500SPSTXDLCSDLCStnTable
cdx6500SPSTXDLCSDLCStnTable.description: All of the statistics parameters relevant to the XDLC SDLC Station table.

cdx6500SPSTXDLCSDLCStnEntry.name: cdx6500SPSTXDLCSDLCStnEntry
cdx6500SPSTXDLCSDLCStnEntry.description: A row of XDLC SDLC Station statistics parameters.

cdx6500xdlcsdlcStatsPortNum.name: cdx6500xdlcsdlcStatsPortNum
cdx6500xdlcsdlcStatsPortNum.description: Refers to the physical port number.

cdx6500xdlcsdlcUtilizationIn.name: cdx6500xdlcsdlcUtilizationIn
cdx6500xdlcsdlcUtilizationIn.description: Indicates the percentage of station resources currently in use from the line to the port.

cdx6500xdlcsdlcUtilizationOut.name: cdx6500xdlcsdlcUtilizationOut
cdx6500xdlcsdlcUtilizationOut.description: Indicates the percentage of station resources currently in use from the port to the line.

cdx6500xdlcsdlcCharInTotal.name: cdx6500xdlcsdlcCharInTotal
cdx6500xdlcsdlcCharInTotal.description: Total number of characters processed until now, not including header characters.
